subSubSection.paragraph:
Head. Transverse, width of head twice its lateral length, and 1.4 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 24I
); antenna with 36 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.5 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere5.0, 3.5 and 2.0 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 24F
); length of maxillary palp 0.8 × height of head (
Fig. 23
); eye in dorsal view 2.7 × as long as temple (
Fig. 24I
); eye in lateral view 1.1 × higher than wide; frons smooth posteriorly, but rugose between antennal sockets (
Fig. 24K
); vertex and temple smooth; OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 8:3:3; face densely granulate, 1.8 × wider than high, rather convex medially and with a longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 24J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and with some punctures (
Fig. 24J
); mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 24L
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobe-shaped (
Fig. 24M
), middle tooth curved and acute, with no incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 24L
), medial length of mandible 1.7 × its maximum width.

Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.4 × its height (
Fig. 24B
); pronope absent; medio-anteriorly pronotum crenulate, remainder of pronotum smooth; epicnemial area crenulated; precoxal sulcus widely crenulate, reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area (
Fig. 24B
); pleural sulcus narrowly crenulated; episternal scrobe linear and deep; metapleuron densely reticulate-rugose; middle lobe of mesoscutum densely setose (
Fig. 24C
); notauli incomplete, absent on disc (
Fig. 24C
); medio-posterior depression deep and droplet-shaped, not extending to middle of mesoscutum, scutellar sulcus deep, with three longitudinal carinae, sulcus 3.0 × wider than its maximum length (
Fig. 24C
); scutellum smooth; surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent posteriorly (
Fig. 24D
).

Wings (
Fig. 24A
). Pterostigma wide, 3.3 × longer than its maximum width. r:3-SR:SR1 = 5:20:52; 1-SR+M nearly straight; SR1 straight; r 0.4 × as long as width of pterostigma; cu-a postfurcal; 1-CU1:2-CU1 = 3: 20; 3-CU1 as long as CU1b; 2-SR:3-SR:r-m = 9:9:5; m-cu interstitial, converging to 1-M posteriorly; first subdiscal cell 4.0 × as long as wide; M+CU1 largely unsclerotized. Hind wing: M+CU: 1-M: 1r-m = 20:15:13; m-cu antefurcal.

Legs. Hind coxa smooth, without ventro-basal tubercle; tarsal claws slender, longer than arolium (
Fig. 24N
); length of femur, tibia and basitarsus of hind leg 5.0, 9.0 and 6.7 × their width, respectively; apical appendages of hind tarsal segments absent, segments ventrally with dense bristles (
Fig. 24N
).

Metasoma. Length of first tergite 2.4 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate, its dorsal carinae parallel posteriorly (
Fig. 24D
); dorsope distinct; convexity of upper valve of ovipositor rather steep basally (
Fig. 24H
); setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.38 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.4 times), and 1.2 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 24H
).

Colour. Black (
Fig. 23
); two basal segments of antenna and mandible yellowish brown; palpi yellow; subapically antenna with 5–10 whitish segments (
Fig. 24G
); metasoma and legs yellow, but first tergite black, posterior part of second–sixth tergite brownish, and apical part of hind femur, hind tibia and tarsus dark brown; pterostigma and veins brown; wing membrane hyaline.
